Check and manage Windermere Cloudflare product image regeneration.

## What this skill does

Checks progress on the Windermere CF image regeneration scripts, restarts them if stopped, and rebuilds the review gallery.

## Step 1 — Check status

```bash
python3 -c "
import json, os
for label, path in [('Batch 1 (v1)', '/tmp/windermere-regen-progress.json'), ('Batch 2 (v2)', '/tmp/windermere-regen-v2-progress.json')]:
    if os.path.exists(path):
        p = json.load(open(path))
        print(f'{label}: Done={len(p[\"done\"])} Failed={len(p[\"failed\"])}')
        if p['failed']: print(f'  Failed: {p[\"failed\"][:5]}')
    else:
        print(f'{label}: not started')
"
pgrep -f generate-windermere-images && echo "process running" || echo "process stopped"
```

## Step 2 — Restart if stopped

If v2 not finished:
```bash
# Clear failures for retry
python3 -c "
import json
p = json.load(open('/tmp/windermere-regen-v2-progress.json'))
p['failed'] = []
json.dump(p, open('/tmp/windermere-regen-v2-progress.json', 'w'), indent=2)
"
# Start in background
cd /tmp && python3 /tmp/generate-windermere-images-v2.py >> /tmp/windermere-regen-v2.log 2>&1 &
```

## Step 3 — Rebuild gallery and open

```bash
python3 /tmp/build-gallery.py && open /tmp/windermere-gallery.html
```

